Step Four: Insight Generation

Data Interpretation:

Based on the data acquired for the five locations The tourist company is offering trip plans for we can say the following concerning the weather patterns.

Out of the Five locations Antigua is consistently the hottest with an average temperature of 82.64°F over a 6 day period and an average humidity level of 76.93% and with the fastest wind speeds of 17.48 meter per second.

Berlin has an average daily temperature of 43.85°F and a humidity level of 70.36% with relatively low wind speeds of 5.14m/s compared to the other four locations.

Amsterdam has an average daily temperature of 46.02°F and humidity level of 82.15% that increase with dropping temperatures, and a wide spread of wind speeds averaging at 6.37m/s.

London and Vancouver have similar temperatures (averaging 48.56°F and 49.83°F respectively) with Vancouver maintaining a higher humidity level with a smaller spread than London (averaging 78.48% and 87.51%), and both locations maintain low wind speeds(averaging 5.6m/s and 6.97m/s).

All the locations maintain a stronger correlation between temperature and humidity. Vancouver is the only location to have a stronger correlation between humidity and wind speed. Amsterdam has the strongest correlations between all three categories.

Redommendations

Based on the data collected and the insights extracted I would recommend the tourist company promote these five locations and advise their customers on the following.

Antigua

Best Time to Visit: Winter and spring.

Antigua is the spot to be for those customers that want to experience the sun and the sea to their fullest. It has hot winters and hotter summers which makes it a great destination for escaping harsh winters. Definitely swimwear and shorts are a must when traveling to Antigua to experience all the Island has to offer with its 365 beaches. With the strong winds it’s a great location for parasailing, sail boating, and sailboarding.

Berlin

Best Time to Visit: Fall and Winter

Berlin in November is a cool environments with high humidity which has the makings for a beautiful winter vacation. Although it is unlikely for snowfall until further into December the mild temperatures and low wind speeds could be very attractive to those customers in more extreme heat looking to cool off, but not too much. Plan for the cold by packing extra layers and cold weather clothing. Berlins a great location in the fall and winter to touring the historic sites and enjoying the traditional foods and drinks to stay warm while enjoying the fresh cool air.

Amsterdam, London, Vancouver

Best Time to Visit: Fall and Spring

Amsterdam, London, and Vancouver are all very similar in temperature, humidity, and wind speed. Much like Berlin they are great cold weather destinations for those looking to escape the heat and experience the winter season. What make these locations different is their wind speeds which contribute to the temperatures feeling colder then they actually are. Pack cold weather cloths and remember to bring your knit cap and scarf to save your ears and nose. All three cities have plenty to do that will keep the cold away as you explore the sights and experience the multicultural restaurants.
